textBeforeTable: Notre Dame Head Coach Jay Louderback "I thought we played really well today. The key for us was winning at No. 1 doubles. They (Missouri) have a really good No. 1 doubles team, but we played unbelievably well today. When you get into the NCAA Tournament and you have two good teams going at it, the doubles point is such a key." "It was great for Alicia (Salas) and Sarah Jane (Connelly) to get up as fast as they did (at No. 2 and No. 4 singles). That really took the pressure off our other singles players. I also thought Kristina (Stastny) did a great job fighting back to win her first set that put us in four of the six singles and got us rolling in a hurry." Missouri Head Coach Blake Starkey "The doubles point was the key to the match. We were very off at the No. 1 doubles spot. It's atypical for us to lose at that spot and it sort of set the tone for the entire match." "In the singles, we didn't lose, we just ran out of time. Notre Dame played well and they are a very good team. They just outplayed us in some spots." "The NCAA Tournament is just another match, but it just has 'NCAA' in front of it.
